Vice President Mike Pence spoke at the 10th annual CEO Council of the Wall Street Journal, thanking business leaders for their investment in America's future and providing an update on the progress of the Trump administration. Pence highlighted the administration's efforts to roll back federal regulations, unleash American energy, pursue fair and reciprocal trade agreements, and appoint strict constructionists to federal courts. He emphasized the need for tax cuts and tax reform, stating that the administration aims to cut taxes for working families, simplify the tax code, and make the economy more competitive by lowering the corporate tax rate. Pence urged business leaders to communicate the importance of tax cuts to their employees and to support the administration's efforts to pass tax reform. He also addressed questions about trade policy and North Korea.